{{unreferenced|date=April 2011}}
'''YUTEL for Peace''' ({{lang-sh|italic=yes|YUTEL za mir}}) was an [[anti-war movement|anti-war]] concert organized by the independent Yugoslav National Broadcasting Agency [[Yutel]], held at the [[Olympic Hall Zetra|Zetra Arena]] in [[Sarajevo]] on Sunday, 28 July 1991 as a protest against the [[Yugoslav wars|war in Yugoslavia]]. The following artists played at the concert: [[Rade Šerbedžija]], [[Bajaga i Instruktori]], [[Crvena Jabuka]], [[Goran Bregović]], [[Haris Džinović]], [[Ekatarina Velika|EKV]], [[Dino Merlin]], [[Indexi]], [[Regina (singer)|Regina]], [[Nele Karajlić]], [[Plavi Orkestar]] and others.
The Concert was originally planned outdoors at the plateau in front of the [[Holiday Inn]] hotel, but was subsequently moved to the Zetra arena because of bad weather conditions. The concert was attended by over thirty thousand spectators, with another fifty thousand left outside of the sold-out venue. The program was hosted by YUTEL [[News presenter|news anchors]] [[Goran Milić]] and [[Gordana Suša]]. The broadcast was only aired in [[Socialist Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina|SR Bosnia-Herzegovina]] and [[Socialist Republic of Macedonia|SR Macedonia]] because the other four channels of the [[Yugoslav Radio Television|Yugoslav national public broadcasting system]] (JRT) refused to carry it.
