{{refimprove|date=May 2017}}
'''''The Art of Success''''' is a play by the British playwright [[Nick Dear]], centered on the life of [[William Hogarth]]. It premiered at the [[Royal Shakespeare Company]] in 1986, with [[Michael Kitchen]] playing Hogarth and [[Niamh Cusack]] playing his wife, Jane. It premiered to an American audience at the [[Manhattan Theatre Club]], with [[Tim Curry]] playing Hogarth and [[Mary-Louise Parker]] playing Jane. Both productions were directed by [[Adrian Noble]].

